  "response": "If someone is caught laundering money, they can face serious legal consequences, including:\n\n1. Criminal Charges\n- Federal money laundering charges\n- Potential felony conviction\n- Significant prison time (typically 10-20 years)\n- Large monetary fines\n\n2. Financial Penalties\n- Seizure of assets involved in laundering\n- Substantial financial penalties\n- Potential forfeitures\n\n3. Additional Consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty obtaining future employment\n- Potential deportation for non-citizens\n\n4. Investigation Process\n- Potential federal investigation\n- Forensic financial analysis\n- Possible involvement of agencies like FBI, IRS\n\nThe specific penalties depend on the amount of money, specific circumstances, and jurisdiction.",
